{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbfa8e1d9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12894"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"12894"},"text":"§ 12894.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Homeownership program requirements","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbfa8e1da-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12894/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A homeownership program under this part shall provide for acquisition by eligible families of ownership interests in, or shares representing, units in an eligible property under any arrangement determined by the Secretary to be appropriate, such as cooperative ownership (including limited equity cooperative ownership) and fee simple ownership (including condominium ownership), for occupancy by the eligible families.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbfa8e1db-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12894/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Affordability","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A homeownership program under this part shall provide for the establishment of sales prices (including principal, insurance, taxes, and interest and closing costs) for initial acquisition of the property, and for sales to eligible families, such that the eligible family shall not be required to expend more than 30 percent of the adjusted income of the family per month to complete a sale under the homeownership program.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbfa8e1dc-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12894/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Eligible property","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A property may not participate in a homeownership program under this part unless all tenants or occupants of the property (at the time of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn004129"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn004129"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" So in original. The word “of” probably should not appear."}],"tail":" the application for the implementation grant covering the property is filed with the Secretary) participate in the homeownership program."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbfa8e1dd-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12894/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Plan","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"A homeownership program under this part shall provide, and include a plan, for—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfa8e1de-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12894/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" identifying and selecting eligible families to participate in the homeownership program;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfa8e1df-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12894/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" providing relocation assistance to families who elect to move; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfa8e1e0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12894/d/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" ensuring continued affordability of the property to homebuyers and homeowners.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbfa8e1e1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12894/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Housing quality standards","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The application shall include a plan ensuring that the unit—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfa8e1e2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12894/e/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" will be free from any defects that pose a danger to health or safety before transfer of an ownership interest in, or shares representing, a unit to an eligible family; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfa8e1e3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12894/e/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" will, not later than 2 years after the transfer to an eligible family, meet minimum housing standards established by the Secretary for the purpose of this title.","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn004130"},"text":"2","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn004130"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"2","children":[],"tail":" So in original. See References in Text note below."}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbfa8e1e4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12894/f"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Preference for acquisition of vacant units","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Each homeownership program under this part shall provide that, in making vacant units in eligible properties available for acquisition by eligible families, preference shall be given to eligible families who reside in public or Indian housing.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbfa8e1e5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/625/tIV/s444"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–625, title IV, § 444","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-28"},"text":"Nov. 28, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/4176"},"text":"104 Stat. 4176","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/550/tI/s181/f"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–550, title I, § 181(f)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-28"},"text":"Oct. 28, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/3736"},"text":"106 Stat. 3736","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbfa8e1e6-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbfa8e1e7-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idbfa8e1e8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This title, referred to in subsec. (e)(2), is title IV of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/625"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–625","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-28"},"text":"Nov. 28, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/4148"},"text":"104 Stat. 4148","children":[],"tail":", known as the Homeownership and Opportunity Through HOPE Act, which enacted this subchapter and subchapter II–A (§ 1437aaa et seq.) of chapter 8 of this title, amended sections 1437c, 1437f, 1437"},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":", 1437p, 1437r, and 1437s of this title and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1709"},"text":"section 1709 of Title 12","children":[],"tail":", Banks and Banking, and enacted provisions set out as notes under sections 1437c, 1437aa, and 1437aaa of this title. For complete classification of title IV to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1437aaa"},"text":"section 1437aaa of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idbfa8e1e9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1992—Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/550"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–550","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (f)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
